 systems.\nIt means we are currently not able to remotely identify faults in the street\nlighting system.\n\n\"The default mode for faults is that the lights stay on to ensure that roads\nare not left completely unlit and become a safety concern. \u201cThere are a number\nof steps required to resolve the problem, and we are working through these as\nquickly as we can.\u201d\n\nShare this on\n\nStory Saved\n\nYou can find this story in My Bookmarks.Or by navigating to the user icon in\nthe top right.\n\nFollow LeicestershireLive\n\nFacebookTwitter\n\nComment\n\nMore On\n\n  * Leicester City Council\n\nEast Midlands TrainsLive travel updates as person hit by train in\nLeicestershireServices in the county have been affected\n\nWork underway on Leicestershire's first 'garden village' - and it includes\nHollywood-style sign\n\nPlanning\n\nAlmost 2,000 homes will feature as part of the major Broadnook development off\nthe A6\n\n'Staffy or XL Bully' attacks man and dog in street\n\nLeicestershire Police\n\nThe man was bitten and the injured pet needed stitches\n\nBlaze at 18th century Queniborough Lodge was arson\n\nLeicestershire Fire and Rescue Service\n\nThe derelict home in Melton Road was set alight on Sunday evening\n\nThird boy arrested after Leicester stabbing\n\nCrime\n\nThree boys aged 16, 15 and 15 have now been arrested after the stabbing of a\nboy who is also 15\n\nAnimalsLeicestershire man banned after birds of prey kept in 'appalling'\nconditionsConcerned members of the public alerted police to the issues in\nEllistown's Whitehall Road\n\n'Staffy or XL Bully' attacks man and dog in street\n\nLeicestershire Police\n\nThe man was bitten and the injured pet needed stitches\n\nTime running out to apply for voter ID in the upcoming police and crime\ncommissioner elections\n\nPolitics\n\nIf you have not got photo ID, the deadline to apply for your voter authority\ncertificate is 5pm tomorrow\n\nITV Emmerdale fans 'work out' who will be killed off after 37 years in